			<td class="BoardRowB" colspan=2 width="83%">
				 <br>  <br> Jaron said in an earlier post <br> &quot;Man, just shut up already.  <br> Why are people camping?  <br> Because your guild, in its infinite wisdom, STARTED CAMPING... VICIOUSLY.  <br>  <br> For every action there is a reaction.  <br>  <br> You camp, and act like total dicks, and people are gonna get sick of it and do whatever it takes to make you stop.  <br> In this case, that means taking the portals away and keeping them away.&quot; <br>  <br> So now you are camping them... Two wrongs now make a right? In your efforts to combat this, you have lowered yourself to their level and even worse. You know it's wrong, you know the effects of it, yet there you are, doing it in the name of righteousness. Perhaps before you go into a moral outrage you should examine your morals as well. <br>  <br> I personally hate the portal camping, and have made a studied effort to avoid Palisades since the BS all started. I have several friends on both sides of this issue, some in CK, and some out there trying to stop the BS. Until patch day, when there will be no more portal camping and this whole stupid issue is laid to rest. I will not actively PK. This whole situation sickens me for the stance both sides have taken. <br>  <br> Swind, True, the rest of CK, good luck, you reap what you sow, I shall not go aganst you in your choices, nor shall I help you.  <br>  <br> Those who believe they are fighting the goodfight, Golden Force, Verlaine, Yarez, careful you do not become what you despise, as you are walking a razors edge now. <br>  <br> My two pyreals worth, Flame on.
