		<tr valign=top>
			<td class="BoardRowB" colspan=2 width="83%">
				Before you put Grey, Yarez, and Tribus on the same level as the Cereal Killers I would like to point out some moral theory here. <br>  <br> Every society creates its own moral standards, whether it be agreed upon by the majority or set down by a dictator. Most would agree that democracy is the best course in creating laws, the majority should set down the law. I'm not going to go into the morality of democracy so I'll assume that people agree that having the majority create laws is the fairest course of action because it takes into account as many people's views as possible.  <br>  <br> With that being said, the majority creates laws that everyone must abide by, including what punishments should be for those that break the law. From a societal standpoint, morality is determined by the majority in the laws, written or unwritten, that it creates. A standard for right and wrong is set.  <br>  <br> From the standpoint of the morningthaw society, the Cereal Killers have broken rules that the majority agree to. As punishment and an effort to keep it from happening again, the majority has agreed that the Cereal Killers should be kept out of palisades at all costs. Therefore, it is now permissible to portal camp CK's to prevent them from doing it to others.  <br>  <br> You say that others have lowered themselves to the CK's standards but there are two important differences between what Grey, Tribus, and Yarez's monarchies do and what the CK's do. The first difference is that the CK's portal camp indiscriminately, their actions have shown that they don't wish to follow the unwritten rules of the MT community and in doing so relinquish their right to be a member of this community. In doing so, they have created a disturbance which the community cannot live with. In order to right this disturbance people have banded together to try to prevent it from happening by driving out the persons responsible and the majority backs these actions. <br>  <br> Second, as I already stated above, these guilds have the backing of the majority, unlike the CK's. The majority has spoken against the actions of the CK's and voiced their approval of such methods to keep the CK's out of pali.  <br>  <br> Some actions, while reprehensible, must be used to protect those that cannot protect themselves. Hence, our justice system uses jails to deprive felons of their liberty, although reprehensible, is necessary. In our community, we do not have the power to restrain them, therefore we must use other means to keep the peace. 		

			</td>
		</tr>
