				Roji  <br> Posts: 1,527 <br> Registered: Jun 00 <br>  Date Posted: 4:47am Subject: RE: One Final Offer from CK - Save your Box Tops Now! - Date Edited: 4:54am (2 edits total) Edited By: Roji   <br> Umm...it still amazed me how seriously some of the parties involved here are taking a game. From my rather detached viewpoint (watching both sides while trying to loose PK pts) the past week has been pretty amusing. A couple of points:  <br>  <br> 1. All the fussing about people camping and preventing people from getting back and forth from E. Gev. is just silly. With the PK timer anyone can get by with at most 5% vitae. Like that's seriously stopping anyone from getting by?!? Quit whining about it please, it's silly. This goes for either side.  <br>  <br> 2. However the whole gank-fest started, there are a large number of people there to kill CK because its fun and they enjoy an excuse to gank without being seen as griefing. The whole thing about keeping the portal clear makes a nice excuse, but thats all it really is (see point 1 above).  <br>  <br> 3. Alot of you take PK way way to seriously. Death means nothing in this game, and there is almost always a vitae healer around. It's not like you're dropping items.  <br>  <br> 4. The whole Pali portal thing gives this game an element of PK it desperately needed. A single point to congregate, defend and fight. People now have a place to go and a 'goal'...hold the portal. With server numbers so low, thats a godsend. Sad that Pali is being made KvK soon.  <br>  <br> 5. Whatever you might think of True and his group, he certainly has met his goal of livening things up. People are there and they look to be having fun. Kudos to True'Tact for that at least.  <br>  <br> -----signature-----  <br>  <br> AC1: Rogi (Archer 71) : Roji (Battlemage 76) : Raoji (Sword/TW 77) : Kittay (TW 65+)  <br> AC2: Anathae (Bounty Hunter 49) : Roji (Mage 17) : Passion (AOE ALchemist 48) : Serene Tao (Mage/Sage 45) : Fluff (Melee/Invoker 43)  <br>   <br> 
