				I'd say that if you weren't there you shouldn't make assumptions about what you think people, in this case Greys, Tribus, Ark and Yarez, were doing last night. In my case it wasn't so much retribution as keeping the route clear for guild members to run through safely. I tried running through on an alt who doesn't have portal recall and got attacked and followed from the drop. Then another two guildmates said the same thing happened to them...so I came back to help clear the drop out.  <br>  <br> If there weren't people there almost every night just attacking anyone and everyone who entered and ran through Palisades there would be no need for anyone to clear out the drop and hold it from miscreants.  <br>  <br> Think of it like Kingdom warfare for an ingame resource such as a mine. In this case it happens to be a travel route (Palisades to East Gevoth) but there is very little difference. This all comes down to holding that resource through KvK means so that you can allow guildmates and friends to safely utilize it.
